## MITOBIM assembly for Micrelenchus tesselatus

### Summary

I tried a couple of approaches. One was to use MITOBIM that iteratively construct an assemblym and one was to use SPADES (an assembler). SPADES performed better by getting more large scaffolds but both left gaps,



### SPADES

Spades is a local assembler. I tried with different subset of reads but it performed best with all the reads.

```
./spades.py --pe1-1 ~/projects/Micrelenchus/trimmed_reads/2420-04-11-01_S4_L001_R1_001_TRIMMED.fastq.gz   --pe1-2 ~/projects/Micrelenchus/trimmed_reads/2420-04-11-01_S4_L001_R2_001_TRIMMED.fastq.gz   -o spadestestMtesselatus
```
	### MITOBIM

	I obtained a lot of contigs, I used them as. a reference for MITOBIM in an attempt to close the gaps.

	I made a small with  12S, 16S and COI available on GENBANK in referencesformitobim/Microlenchus_tesselatus_bait.fa



```
mkdir -p Mtesselatus/3genesref015
seqtk sample -s100 trimmed_reads/2420-04-11-01_S4_L001_R1_001_TRIMMED.fastq.gz  0.15 >  Mtesselatus/2420-04-11-01_S4_L001_R1_001_TRIMMED015.fastq 
seqtk sample -s100 trimmed_reads/2420-04-11-01_S4_L001_R2_001_TRIMMED.fastq.gz  0.15 >  Mtesselatus/2420-04-11-01_S4_L001_R2_001_TRIMMED015.fastq
~/repos/scripts/Micrelenchus/interleave-fasta.py  Mtesselatus/2420-04-11-01_S4_L001_R1_001_TRIMMED015.fastq  Mtesselatus/2420-04-11-01_S4_L001_R2_001_TRIMMED015.fastq   > Mtesselatus/2420-04-11-01_S4_L001_R2_001_TRIMMED_interleavedsub015.fastq

```
```
mkdir -p Mtesselatus/3genesref015
cd Mtesselatus/3genesref015
MITObim.pl --denovo -end 100 --pair -sample Mtesselatus -ref refspades -readpool  ../2420-04-11-01_S4_L001_R2_001_TRIMMED_interleavedsub015.fastq --clean --quick ../../referencesformitobim/Microlenchus_tesselatus_bait.fa
```	


quite good results:

```

readpool contains 29580 reads
assembly contains 9 contig(s)
min contig length: 162 bp
max contig length: 10275 bp
avg contig length: 1701 bp
find details on individual contigs in: /gpfs1m/projects/uoo00116/projects/Micrelenchus/Mtesselatus/3genesref015/iteration10/Mtesselatus-refspades_assembly/Mtesselatus-refspades_d_info/Mtesselatus-refspades_info_contigstats.txt
```


second scaffold is 3144.

